# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# .gitignore — Model B (cancer pipelines)
#
# Rule of thumb: source code, configs, codelists, README → committed.
# Patient data, model artifacts, training outputs, large binaries → LOCAL ONLY.
#
# This file is intentionally aggressive. Add `!path/to/something` at the
# bottom to re-include anything that gets caught accidentally.
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ─── OS / editor noise ──────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
# Stray scratch scripts that shouldn't be tracked
uniquepatients
.ipynb_checkpoints/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.swp
*.swo
.vscode/
.idea/
.claude/

# ─── Logs / caches ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.log
catboost_info/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# ─── Tabular / dataframe data — PHI risk, NEVER commit ─────────────
*.csv
*.tsv
*.parquet
*.feather
*.arrow
*.orc
*.npy
*.npz
*.h5
*.hdf5

# ─── Model artifacts / binaries ────────────────────────────────────
*.pkl
*.pickle
*.joblib
*.keras
*.bin
*.onnx
*.pt
*.pth
*.safetensors

# ─── Archives (often ship model/data bundles) ──────────────────────
*.zip
*.tar
*.tar.gz
*.tgz
*.gz
*.bz2
*.7z

# ─── Common output / results / data directories ────────────────────
# (match anywhere in the tree, regardless of cancer subfolder)
**/results/
**/output/
**/outputs/
**/data/
**/Data_Input/
**/FE_Results/
**/cleanupfeatures/
**/full_outputs/
**/saved_models/
**/json_pilot/
**/scratch/
**/tmp/
**/raw/
_all_cancer_results_*/

# ─── Patient ID lists (PHI even though they're JSON) ───────────────
**/shared_split.json
*_split.json
*_guids.json
*_patient_ids.json

# ─── Jupyter notebooks: only source (no outputs) goes to git ───────
# Notebooks with embedded outputs frequently contain patient-level
# tables, predictions, or plots derived from PHI. Block by default,
# re-include explicitly clean source notebooks (no outputs).
*.ipynb
!**/source_notebooks/*.ipynb

# ─── Re-include codelists (source-of-truth, must be committed) ─────
# These ARE the curated medical code mappings; the rest of the repo
# depends on them. Override the *.csv / *.tsv blanket above.
!**/codelists/
!**/codelists/**
!**/codelist2.0/
!**/codelist2.0/**

# ─── Re-include curated SNOMED mapping sheets (not under codelists/) ──
# Hand-curated SNOMED mapping spreadsheets that live in 1_Top_Snomeds/
# folders. Same risk class as codelists/ — clinical mappings, no PHI.
!**/1_Top_Snomeds/
!**/1_Top_Snomeds/**
